im to solve old and famous questions in 3-dimensional topology. l becomes simpler as the first Betti number increases. As an explicit function of Alexander polynomials and surgery coefficients of framed links, the function F extends in a natural way to framed links in rational homology spheres. It is proven that F describes the variation of l under any surgery starting from a rational homology sphere. Thus F yields a global surgery formula for the Casson invariant.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aMATHEMATICS / Topology.2bisacsh  a3-manifold.  aAddition.  aAlexander polynomial.  aAmbient isotopy.  aBetti number.  aCasson invariant.  aChange of basis.  aChange of variables.  aCobordism.  aCoefficient.  aCombination.  aCombinatorics.  aComputation.  aConjugacy class.  aConnected component (graph theory).  aConnected space.  aConnected sum.  aCup product.  aDeterminant.  aDiagram (category theory).  aDisk (mathematics).  aEmpty set.  aExterior (topology).  aFiber bundle.  aFibration.  aFunction (mathematics).  aFundamental group.  aHomeomorphism.  aHomology (mathematics).  aHomology sphere.  aHomotopy sphere.  aIndeterminate (variable).  aInteger.  aKlein bottle.  aKnot theory.  aManifold.  aMorphism.  aNotation.  aOrientability.  aPermutation.  aPolynomial.  aPrime number.  aProjective plane.  aScientific notation.  aSeifert surface.  aSequence.  aSummation.  aSymmetrization.  aTaylor series.  aTheorem.  aTopology.  aTubular neighborhood.  aUnlink.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Annals of Mathematics eBook-Package 1940-2020z9783110494914oZDB-23-PMB08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org